subCards.title: What Are FGM-148 Anti-Tank Rockets? Latest U.S. Weapons Package for Ukraine
subCards.abstract: President Joe Biden said the US will send a new weapons package to Ukraine worth $500m that will be announced on Feb. 21. In a surprise visit to Kyiv, Biden said the package will include ammunition for howitzer artillery and High Mobility Artillery Rocket Systems (HIMARS). The President said that anti-armour systems, air surveillance radars and FGM-148 Javelin anti-tank rocket systems will be part of the package.

images.title: What Are FGM-148 Anti-Tank Rockets? Latest U.S. Weapons Package for Ukraine

subCards.title: Israelis protest before first judiciary reform vote
subCards.abstract: Thousands took to the streets in Jerusalem and Tel Aviv on Monday (February 20) with the Israeli opposition vowing to "fight for the soul of the nation" as parliament prepared to hold a first reading of judicial changes promoted by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's religious-nationalist government. Polls have found that most Israelis want the reforms slowed to allow for dialog with critics - or shelved altogether.

images.title: Israelis protest before first judiciary reform vote

subCards.title: Watch: Air Raid Sirens Wail As Biden And Zelensky Walk Through Kyiv
subCards.abstract: Air raid sirens rang out through Kyiv as U.S. President Joe Biden and Ukrainian counterpart Volodymyr Zelensky walked through the capital on Monday. Biden made a surprise visit to the city as Ukraine approaches one year since the Russian invasion.

images.title: Watch: Air Raid Sirens Wail As Biden And Zelensky Walk Through Kyiv

subCards.abstract: Biden admin denies US sabotaged Nord Stream Pipelines. John Kirby on Hersh report: Completely false Briahna Joy Gray and Robby Soave react to National Security Council spokesperson John Kirby claimed that Seymour Hersh’s story alleging the U.S. blew up the Nord Stream pipeline is not true. subCards.title: Spinal stimulation could aid mobility after stroke
subCards.abstract: Scientists have long tested spinal stimulators in a quest to help people in wheelchairs stand. Now, University of Pittsburgh researchers hope they may help solve a more common problem: stroke-caused paralysis of arms and hands. (Feb. 20) (AP video: Angie Wang)

images.title: Spinal stimulation could aid mobility after stroke

subCards.title: North Korea launches two short range ballistic missiles
subCards.abstract: North Korea appears to have launched two short range ballistic missiles into the waters off the Korean Peninsula, according to Japanese officials, marking its second missile launch in three days. NBC News’ Janis Mackey Frayer reports.

images.title: North Korea launches two short range ballistic missiles

subCards.title: What would happen if China supports Russia in Ukraine war? Retired lt. col. weighs in
subCards.abstract: Retired Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman shares his thoughts on President Biden's surprise visit to Kyiv and what could happen if China decides to support Russia in the Ukraine war.

images.title: What would happen if China supports Russia in Ukraine war? Retired lt. col. weighs in

subCards.title: Biden makes surprise Ukraine visit, pledging ammo
subCards.abstract: Air raid sirens blared across Ukraine as U.S. President Joe Biden landed in Kyiv for a surprise meeting with President Volodymyr Zelenskiy, ahead of the Russian invasion's one-year anniversary. It comes on the heels of concerns that Ukraine is burning through munitions faster than the West can supply it. Matthew Larotonda reports.

images.title: Biden makes surprise Ukraine visit, pledging ammo

subCards.title: President Biden makes surprise trip to Ukraine
subCards.abstract: President Biden made a surprise visit to Kyiv on Monday to meet with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy just days ahead of the one-year anniversary of Russia’s invasion of the country. NBC News’ Josh Lederman and Erin McLaughlin have the details.

images.title: President Biden makes surprise trip to Ukraine

subCards.title: Burkina Faso marks end of French troops on its soil
subCards.abstract: A flag-lowering ceremony has officially ended French military operations on Burkina Faso's soil - marking a new chapter in the West African country's fight against jihadist militants. David Doyle has more.

images.title: Burkina Faso marks end of French troops on its soil

subCards.title: Hear retired brigadier general explain ‘significance’ of Biden’s visit to Ukraine
subCards.abstract: CNN This Morning anchor Poppy Harlow speaks to retired Brigadier General Steve Anderson to discuss the importance of President Joe Biden's highly secretive visit to Kyiv.

images.title: Hear retired brigadier general explain ‘significance’ of Biden’s visit to Ukraine

subCards.title: Sec. Antony Blinken warns China against giving Russia 'lethal support' in Ukraine
subCards.abstract: President Biden has warned China of "real consequences" if President Xi sends "lethal assistance" to Russia, according to Sec. Antony Blinken.

images.title: Sec. Antony Blinken warns China against giving Russia 'lethal support' in Ukraine

subCards.title: Joe Biden honored with plaque on Kyiv's Walk of the Brave
subCards.abstract: Video from the Ukrainian Presidential Press Service showed President Biden and his host, President Zelenskyy, inspecting a plaque honoring Biden's name on the Walk of the Brave in Kyiv's Constitution Square.

images.title: Joe Biden honored with plaque on Kyiv's Walk of the Brave

subCards.title: Biden Slams Putin During Surprise Kyiv Visit: 'He's Just Been Plain Wrong'
subCards.abstract: U.S. President Joe Biden doubled-down on his commitment to Ukraine during a surprise visit to Kyiv on Monday, and didn't miss the opportunity to condemn Russian President Vladimir Putin. "Putin thought Ukraine was weak and the West was divided," Biden said. "He's just been plain wrong."

images.title: Biden Slams Putin During Surprise Kyiv Visit: 'He's Just Been Plain Wrong'

subCards.title: Toughened by war's scars, Kyiv presses on
subCards.abstract: Signs of calm resilience - be it the bars packed despite the threat of missile and drone attacks, or the guides who have adapted city tours to the dictates of war - have become increasingly commonplace in Ukraine's capital. Nearly a year after it began, Russia's invasion has upended life but also rallied a nation. Olivia Chan has more.

images.title: Toughened by war's scars, Kyiv presses on

subCards.title: ‘He’s Just Been Plain Wrong’: Biden Says of Putin During Visit to Kyiv
subCards.abstract: President Biden said his Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin was wrong for counting on the West to be divided amid Moscow’s offensive in Ukraine. Biden met with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky during a surprise visit to Kyiv. Photo: POOL/via REUTERS

subCards.abstract: President Biden announced an additional $500 million in U.S. aid to Ukraine during a visit to Kyiv on Monday. CBS News senior foreign correspondent Charlie D'Agata joined Vladimir Duthiers and Anne-Marie Green to discuss the significance of this previously unannounced visit.

images.title: Biden promises $500M in aid to Ukraine during surprise visit to Kyiv

subCards.title: Senator Bernie Sanders on new book, Social Security and the future of jobs
subCards.abstract: Vermont independent Senator Bernie Sanders joins "CBS Mornings" to discuss his new book, "It's OK to Be Angry About Capitalism." He talks about the future of Social Security and his experiences with former President Jimmy Carter.

subCards.abstract: President Biden makes an unannounced trip to Ukraine nearly one year after Russia's invasion. Also, Washington has indications that China may provide weapons to Russia.

subCards.title: At 98 years old, former President Jimmy Carter decides to seek hospice care
subCards.abstract: In a statement, the Carter Center revealed that 98-year-old former President Jimmy Carter has "decided to spend his remaining time at home with his family and receive hospice care." Robert Costa reports from Carter's hometown of Plains, Georgia.

subCards.abstract: People on streets of Kyiv reacted with joy to the unannounced visit of President Joe Biden to Ukraine. During his meeting with the Ukrainian president, Biden promised to stand with Ukraine as long as it takes. Photo: Dimitar Dilkoff/AFP/Getty Images

subCards.title: U.S. alleges China is considering providing lethal aid to Russia
subCards.abstract: Secretary of State Antony Blinken accused China of providing non-lethal aid to Russia in its invasion of Ukraine, adding that Beijing could be considering providing lethal aid to Moscow. NBC News’ Dan De Luce and Janis Mackey Frayer explain what kind of support China could be sending to Russia and how Beijing is reacting to the allegation.

subCards.title: U.S. concerned that China considering support for Russian war effort
subCards.abstract: Secretary of State Antony Blinken said he is "concerned" that China is considering supporting Russia's war in Ukraine with "lethal assistance" and warned there would be "real consequences" for China.

images.title: U.S. concerned that China considering support for Russian war effort

subCards.title: Zelensky: 'The More Russia Loses In Bakhmut, Donbas, Sooner We Can End War'
subCards.abstract: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky acknowledged that the situation in Bakhmut, Vuhledar, Donbas region is still difficult. In his nightly video address to the nation on Sunday, he said that "We are fighting. We are breaking the invader and inflicting extremely tangible losses on Russia."
